headline: F5 Networks (FFIV) Q3 Earnings and Revenues Beat Estimates

headline: F5 (NASDAQ:FFIV) Reports Bullish Q2, Stock Soars
summary: Network application delivery and security specialist F5 (NASDAQ:FFIV) reported Q2 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 12.2% year on year to $780.4 million. Guidance for next quarter’s revenue was better than expected at $790 million at the midpoint, 1.9% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.16 per share was 18.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: F5: Fiscal Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The average estimate of seven analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $3.49 per share. The computer networking company posted revenue of $780.4 million in the period, also topping Street forecasts. Six analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $753.1 million.
